point : maintaining bush tax cut would cost the government 680 billion in revenue over the next ten year accord to paul krugman . 
counterpoint : under current economic circumstance , the deficit be bad , and a downgrade of the credit rating have bad effect . however , stimulation of the economy during a recession be need more . 
point : the tax cut that be create under a republican government can be strongly link with the republican power base . the republican party relies on a relatively small number of very rich and powerful donor . a tax cut for these people often lead to an increase in fund for the republican party . republican representation among the other class generally come from other conservative policy a oppose to one fiscal policy . 
counterpoint : the american system be one that can be change with a popular vote . further , the competition between the two party and the bid to be re elected cause them to make decision that be good for the country so that they be credit for that by the people . 
point : the removal of tax cut for the rich will help create great equality in the u . s . 
counterpoint : as be mention in argument two of the opposition , if tax increase for the rich cause them to leave the country then it be entirely possible that this will lead to even less parity between those leave behind and the poor who have to make do with even less tax revenue through redistribution . 
